### Create Collection!
You need to create a Qdrant Collection as follows:

* Go to http[s]:\//<qdrant_url>/dashboard#/console
If you are hosting locally, this is usually http://localhost:6333/dashboard#/console
* Copy the following into the left panel. This will tell Qdrant to create a new collection called “contextual_retrieval_example”. You can change this of course but you’ll also need to change all “collectionName” references in the template as well!

```
PUT collections/contextual_retrieval_example
{
  "vectors": {
    "default": {
      "distance": "Cosine",
      "size": 1024
    }
  },
  "sparse_vectors": {
    "bm42": {
      "modifier": "idf"
    }
  }
}
```

